## 1. Background Service Persistence (Battery Saver Override)

### 1.1 Current Implementation

[sms_background_service.dart](file:///c:/Users/geral/Downloads/Flutter%20Projects/JJ-Clover-SMS-Booking---Dispatch-System/lib/data/services/sms_background_service.dart) uses the `telephony` plugin's `listenIncomingSms()` to receive SMS messages. The service is a **Dart-level singleton** — it has no native Android foreground service, no wake lock, and no battery optimization exemption.

```dart
// sms_background_service.dart:26-37
Future<void> startListening() async {
  if (_isListening) return;
  _telephony.listenIncomingSms(
    onNewMessage: (SmsMessage msg) {
      _processIncomingSms(msg);  // Dart callback — dies with the app process
    },
  );
  _isListening = true;
}
```

### 1.2 Ghost Test Results

| Scenario | Expected | Actual | Result |
|---|---|---|---|
| App in foreground | SMS received & processed | ⚠️ Service never started | 🔴 FAIL |
| App in background (recent) | SMS received & processed | Process alive but no listener | 🔴 FAIL |
| App killed / swiped away | SMS processed via background isolate | No isolate registered | 🔴 FAIL |
| Battery Saver ON | SMS still processed | No battery exemption | 🔴 FAIL |
| Device reboot | Service auto-restarts | No boot receiver | 🔴 FAIL |

### 1.3 Root Causes

> [!CAUTION]
> The background service is **never initialized** anywhere. [main.dart](file:///c:/Users/geral/Downloads/Flutter%20Projects/JJ-Clover-SMS-Booking---Dispatch-System/lib/main.dart) does not call `SmsBackgroundService.instance.startListening()`.

| Issue | Severity | File |
|---|---|---|
| [startListening()](file:///c:/Users/geral/Downloads/Flutter%20Projects/JJ-Clover-SMS-Booking---Dispatch-System/lib/data/services/sms_background_service.dart#26-38) never called in app lifecycle | 🔴 Critical | [main.dart](file:///c:/Users/geral/Downloads/Flutter%20Projects/JJ-Clover-SMS-Booking---Dispatch-System/lib/main.dart) |
| No `flutter_background_service` integration (declared but unused) | 🔴 Critical | [pubspec.yaml](file:///c:/Users/geral/Downloads/Flutter%20Projects/JJ-Clover-SMS-Booking---Dispatch-System/pubspec.yaml) |
| No foreground service / notification channel | 🔴 Critical | [AndroidManifest.xml](file:///c:/Users/geral/Downloads/Flutter%20Projects/JJ-Clover-SMS-Booking---Dispatch-System/android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml) |
| Missing `FOREGROUND_SERVICE` permission | 🔴 Critical | AndroidManifest.xml |
| Missing `REQUEST_IGNORE_BATTERY_OPTIMIZATIONS` permission | 🔴 Critical | AndroidManifest.xml |
| Missing `RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED` permission | 🟡 High | AndroidManifest.xml |
| No `onBackgroundMessage` handler for `telephony` plugin | 🔴 Critical | sms_background_service.dart |
| [stopListening()](file:///c:/Users/geral/Downloads/Flutter%20Projects/JJ-Clover-SMS-Booking---Dispatch-System/lib/data/services/sms_background_service.dart#39-43) only sets a boolean flag, doesn't unsubscribe | 🟡 Medium | sms_background_service.dart |

### 1.4 Required Fixes for Battery Saver Override

**AndroidManifest.xml** — Add these permissions and service declarations:
```xml
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE_DATA_SYNC" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.REQUEST_IGNORE_BATTERY_OPTIMIZATIONS" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WAKE_LOCK" />
```

**main.dart** — Initialize the background service:
```dart
Future<void> main() async {
  WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized();
  await initializeBackgroundService();  // from flutter_background_service
  await Permission.sms.request();
  // Request battery optimization exemption
  await Permission.ignoreBatteryOptimizations.request();
  runApp(const MyApp());
}
```

**sms_background_service.dart** — Register a top-level `onBackgroundMessage` handler:
```dart
// Top-level function (outside any class) for background isolate
@pragma('vm:entry-point')
void onBackgroundMessage(SmsMessage message) async {
  // Process SMS even when app is killed
  final parsed = SmsParser.parse(message.body ?? '');
  // ... handle command
}
```

