## Summary & Recommendations

### Priority Matrix

| # | Action | Category | Effort | Impact |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Wire up `SmsBackgroundService.startListening()` in [main.dart](file:///c:/Users/geral/Downloads/Flutter%20Projects/JJ-Clover-SMS-Booking---Dispatch-System/lib/main.dart) | Persistence | Low | 🔴 Blocker |
| 2 | Integrate `flutter_background_service` for foreground service | Persistence | Medium | 🔴 Critical |
| 3 | Add `FOREGROUND_SERVICE` + battery exemption permissions | Persistence | Low | 🔴 Critical |
| 4 | Register `onBackgroundMessage` handler with `telephony` plugin | Persistence | Medium | 🔴 Critical |
| 5 | Add quantity range validation (1–100) in [SmsParser](file:///c:/Users/geral/Downloads/Flutter%20Projects/JJ-Clover-SMS-Booking---Dispatch-System/lib/data/services/sms_parser.dart#17-62) | Regex | Low | 🟡 Important |
| 6 | Preserve original casing for address field | Regex | Low | 🟡 Nice-to-have |
| 7 | Add `RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED` + boot receiver | Persistence | Medium | 🟡 Important |
| 8 | Add unit tests for all regex edge cases | Regex | Low | 🟡 Important |

### Overall Verdict

> [!WARNING]
> **Background Service Persistence: FAIL.** The SMS listener infrastructure exists in code but is completely disconnected — it is never started, has no Android-level persistence, and will not survive battery saver, app kill, or device reboot. This must be resolved before the system can function as an automated SMS dispatch.

> [!NOTE]
> **Regex Accuracy: PARTIAL PASS (13/16 cases).** The core parsing logic is correct for standard inputs. Edge cases around zero/overflow quantities and address casing need hardening, but these are low-risk in the current user base.
